comments.text: T215Y/F cause intermediate/high-level resistance to AZT and d4T, low-level resistance to ddI, and potentially low-level resistance to ABC and TDF. T215S/C/D/E/I/V/N/A/L do not reduce NRTI susceptibility but arise from viruses that once contained T215Y/F. The presence of one of these revertant mutations suggests that the patient may have once had a majority virus population with T215Y/F.
